122
00:04:10,721 --> 00:04:12,501
and there's benefits to what we do.

123
00:04:13,122 --> 00:04:14,502
One of the things we're always trying to think about

124
00:04:14,542 --> 00:04:15,502
is where is the camera?

125
00:04:15,542 --> 00:04:16,463
Who's operating the camera?

126
00:04:16,483 --> 00:04:17,143
Who's holding it?

127
00:04:19,370 --> 00:04:20,911
based on the answer to that question,

128
00:04:21,251 --> 00:04:23,613
it'll define how the camera functions

129
00:04:23,653 --> 00:04:25,635
with a little bit of frequency and a little bit of noise.

130
00:04:26,456 --> 00:04:29,578
To aid in the animation work and make our job faster,

131
00:04:30,079 --> 00:04:31,980
we don't hand animate all that all the time.

132
00:04:32,421 --> 00:04:33,542
We have a number of different sliders

133
00:04:33,562 --> 00:04:35,103
here that you can kind of see in this initial column.

134
00:04:35,523 --> 00:04:37,525
