135
00:04:37,585 --> 00:04:41,268
to dial in the weights of a number of different frequency

136
00:04:41,909 --> 00:04:43,831
or a number of different wavelengths that apply

137
00:04:43,911 --> 00:04:46,132
to the translation channels on the camera.

138
00:04:46,753 --> 00:04:47,934
So for instance, shake.

139
00:04:48,234 --> 00:04:53,341
is something that you'd often use if you were in a helicopter shot where the operator might be

140
00:04:53,381 --> 00:04:56,886
sitting there and something that's vibrating and wave is something we use often when we're trying

141
00:04:56,906 --> 00:05:01,311
to do a little bit of handheld. The other advantage that we or the other addition that we've added to

142
00:05:01,351 --> 00:05:01,792
our camera

