334
00:12:59,973 --> 00:13:01,754
an impact of a fist hitting the face.

335
00:13:02,275 --> 00:13:04,837
And then on a cut, the next shot will show

336
00:13:05,177 --> 00:13:06,839
three or four frames prior to that impact,

337
00:13:06,859 --> 00:13:07,659
so you're seeing it twice.

338
00:13:07,799 --> 00:13:09,000
Now the audience doesn't catch that,

339
00:13:09,401 --> 00:13:11,202
but it adds importance to that shot.

340
00:13:11,342 --> 00:13:12,704
It adds importance to that action,

341
00:13:12,864 --> 00:13:15,466
and it helps to sell what's happening in the scene.

342
00:13:17,768 --> 00:13:19,769
So in addition to editing, when it comes to timing.

